      ],
      "section": [
        "Qin",
        "History"
      ],
      "text": "When the Fire Nation first threatened to burn down the Northern Air Temple, Qin was able to secure the services of the mechanist, who offered to help the Fire Nation in their war effort in exchange for the preservation of the temple. Qin visited the temple regularly to check on his inventions, and their partnership led to the creation of destructive tanks and warships."
    },
    {
      "body": "When an impatient Qin visited the Northern Air Temple in early 100 ${link_0}, he was forced away by ${link_1} ${link_2}, but before exiting, he warned them that the Fire Nation would burn the temple to rubble. The ${link_3} refugees that lived in the temple put up a brave fight, and with the mechanist's latest invention - a ${link_4} - they managed to push the invaders back completely. During this battle, however, ${link_5} and the mechanist were forced to abandon the balloon which crashed in the nearby valley. Qin discovered the balloon and quickly learned its importance, stating that \"this defeat [would be] the gateway to many victories.\" After the discovery of the hot air balloon, Qin turned it into a frequently used war balloon, enabling the Fire Nation to control the skies, as well as the land.",
