      "text": "After the destruction of the drill, Qin worked to make more war balloons, while adapting and improving the technology to create the larger Fire Nation airships."
    },
    {
      "body": "During the ${link_0} of the ${link_1} on the ${link_2}, Qin was strolling down the halls of Fire Lord ${link_3}'s secret bunker, where he came across Aang, ${link_4}, and Sokka for a third time. When threatened by them, he quickly gave them directions to Ozai's chambers, where not Ozai but ${link_5} ${link_6} awaited them. After this encounter, Qin resumed his stroll down the hall, whistling as though nothing had occurred. When the eclipse ended, the fruition of Qin's hand in the engineering, manufacturing, and improvement of war balloons was revealed as massive metal airships successfully bombed the invaders' ${link_7}, preventing the majority of the invasion force from escaping.",
